<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-01-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-01-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="199" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d199">
                            <head><persName type="from">Laird Brothers</persName> to <persName type="to">her Majesty’s Treasury</persName>.</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Birkenhead Iron Works,</hi>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Birkenhead,</hi></placeName>
                                    <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-01-09"><hi rend="italic">January</hi> 9, 1864.</date></dateline></opener>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> We wrote to you on the 30th December,
                                drawing attention to our letter of 22d December, respecting the
                                insurance on the El Tousson and El Monnassir, and asking a reply
                                thereto.</p>
                            <p>As we have not yet received any communication on the subject, we
                                would again respectfully ask an early reply.</p>
                            <p>We are, sir, your obedient servants,</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>LAIRD BROTHERS.</signed></closer>
                            <postscript>
                                <p>The <hi rend="smallcaps">Secretary to the Treasury.</hi></p>
                            </postscript>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>